annotationA: Putative ATP-dependent RNA helicase me31b; Unwinds RNA in an ATP-dependent fashion (Potential). Involved in germ cell formation
annotationB: Pop2, isoform E; Protein binding; poly(A)-specific ribonuclease activity; nucleic acid binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: mRNA catabolic process; neuron development; muscle organ development; regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter; mitotic G2 DNA damage checkpoint; neurogenesis; nuclear-transcribed mRNA poly(A) tail shortening; negative regulation of translation
